.TH _printf 3 "March 2026" "Holberton School" "_printf manual"
.SH NAME
_printf \- produces output according to a format

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.PP
.B int _printf(const char *format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B _printf
function produces output according to a format string.

The format string is composed of zero or more directives.
If a character is not a percent sign, it is printed directly.
The conversion specifiers supported by
.B _printf
are:

.TP
.B %c
Prints a single character.

.TP
.B %s
Prints a string.

.TP
.B %%
Prints a percent sign.

.PP
If the format specifier is not recognized, the percent sign and the unknown specifier are printed.

.SH RETURN VALUE
Upon successful return,
.B _printf
returns the number of characters printed, excluding the terminating null byte.

If
.I format
is NULL, or if a percent sign is followed by the end of the string,
.B _printf
returns -1.

.SH EXAMPLES
.B _printf("Character: %c\\n", 'A');
.PP
Character: A

.B _printf("String: %s\\n", "Hello");
.PP
String: Hello

.B _printf("Percent: %%\\n");
.PP
Percent: %

.SH FILES
.I main.h
Header file containing the prototype of
.B _printf

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR printf (3)

